{"id": "1670", "post": "<div class=\"post-1670 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-virtual-servers tag-hostpolar-com tag-new-york tag-openvz\" id=\"post-1670\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/hostpolar-4-99-256mb-openvz-vps-in-new-york/\" rel=\"bookmark\">HostPolar \u2013 $4.99 256MB OpenVZ VPS in New York</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAMPDwwAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" alt=\"Tags: \"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/hostpolar-com/\" rel=\"tag\">hostpolar.com</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/new-york/\" rel=\"tag\">new york</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/openvz/\" rel=\"tag\">openvz</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAMPDwwAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" alt=\"Date/Time: \"> March 4, 2011 @ 2:20 am, by LowEndAdmin</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><a href=\"http://www.hostpolar.com/\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAMPDwwAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=\" data-src=\"/media/images/hostpolar.jpg\" class=\"screenshot\"></a> <a href=\"http://www.hostpolar.com/\"><b>HostPolar</b></a> sent me a request to have their <a href=\"http://hostpolar.com/vps.htm\">VPS hosting plans</a> listed on LowEndBox. They are also offering a special promo \u2014 use coupon code <b>Level2</b> to get a free upgrade from Level1 to Level2. <a href=\"https://hostpolar.com/clients/cart.php?a=add&amp;pid=16&amp;promocode=Level2\">Order Level1 here</a>, and you\u2019ll get</p><ul><li>256MB guaranteed/512MB burstable memory</li><li>15GB storage</li><li>100GB/month data transfer</li><li>OpenVZ/SolusVM</li></ul><p>Servers in New York City with <a href=\"http://welinknyc.com/\">WeLink</a>. From their <a href=\"http://www.hostpolar.com/about.htm\">about us page</a> they were founded in March 2011 (i.e. just a few days ago!) Doing a search on WHT <a href=\"http://www.webhostingtalk.com/showthread.php?t=1025950\">reveals this discussion thread</a>, where a customer did not get what he has ordered, but eventually got refunded. Customer support in this case sounds quite alright.</p><p>Digging a bit deeper, however reveals that it\u2019s the same owner that <a href=\"/blog/blue-shore-host-6-99-xen-vps-with-256mb/\">sent me info on Blue Shore Host</a> a year ago (selling $7 Xen VPS in San Jose). Blue Shore Host, which was run by Jane and Laura <a href=\"http://www.webhostingtalk.com/showthread.php?t=906478\">according to this post</a>, has since been sold to QuickPacket. User \u201cJDAnswer\u201d has also posted offers from other web hosts possibly started by her.</p><p>Cute bear though :P</p><p><b>Update</b>: Use promo code <b>LowEndBox</b> to get 25% off recurring discount.</p><p class=\"dpsp-share-text\"></p><div id=\"dpsp-content-bottom\" class=\"dpsp-content-wrapper dpsp-shape-rounded dpsp-column-auto dpsp-has-spacing dpsp-no-labels dpsp-show-on-mobile dpsp-button-style-1 dpsp-has-icon-background dpsp-has-button-background dpsp-show-total-share-count dpsp-show-total-share-count-after\"><ul class=\"dpsp-networks-btns-wrapper dpsp-networks-btns-content dpsp-has-button-icon-animation\"><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fhostpolar-4-99-256mb-openvz-vps-in-new-york%2F&amp;t=HostPolar%20-%20%244.99%20256MB%20OpenVZ%20VPS%20in%20New%20York\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-facebook dpsp-no-label dpsp-first\" title=\"Share on Facebook\"><span class=\"dpsp-network-icon\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-network-label-wrapper\"></span></a></li><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=HostPolar%20-%20%244.99%20256MB%20OpenVZ%20VPS%20in%20New%20York&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fhostpolar-4-99-256mb-openvz-vps-in-new-york%2F&amp;via=LowEndNetw